<paragraph blockId="87.[151,1436,620,828]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,620,647]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Palps not more than 4 times longer than wide. Antero-lateral setae numerous (39â€“139 pairs). Setae 
<emphasis box="[1388,1436,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">dm1</emphasis>
paddle-shaped. Setae 
<emphasis box="[395,443,657,683]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">dm3</emphasis>
absent. Peripheral setae paddle-shaped or leaf-like and arranged in 1 row. Genital series represented by 1 or 3 pairs of setae 
<emphasis box="[549,563,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">g</emphasis>
. Pseudanal series represented by 4 or 6 pairs of obovate-shaped setae 
<emphasis box="[1349,1374,694,719]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">ps</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
